The paper discusses the use of Multi-Agent Systems (MAS) for emergency evacuation simulations, which falls under the category of MAS (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the implementation of modeling and simulation, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses social sciences, which falls under the category of Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the importance of crowd modeling in emergency simulations, which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the framework proposed for crowd simulation modeling, which falls under the category of Graphics (cs.GR).
